From keais j Subject Re Pioneer Laser player In article Reg Neale writes I'm trying to figure out how to operate a Pioneer Laserdisc LD that I bought at a surplus It is reputedly from some kind of computerised viewing and or ordering THere is what may be an HPIB connector on the When I power it up the front panel power light comes on but no activity and the door doesn't Anyone have any experience with this unit or any ideas on how to obtain documentation What you have is one of the LD players from a video game Dragon's Lair Space Ace etc Call Pioneer Technicial Support at least that's the number I called them at and ask for the LD Interface It shows how the parallel interface should be wired and the codes for the commands play pause reject etc The guide is mainly for hooking the player to a computer but with a little work you could build a wired Jim Keais